From the C++11/14/17 specifications, section [support.types]: 

   \"Note that offsetof is required to work as specified even if unary operator& is overloaded for any of the types involved.\"

And inherited from the C99/C11 spec:

   [offsetof()] \"expands to an integer constant expression that has type size_t\"

See also https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/offsetof

